From 2bdf7f8ebad792928ef42ef360157e570fafe2dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 06:30:14 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P3: guest-side shared-memory ring transport
 (task_self_trap)

Guest half of the ring fast path, gated -DDARLING_RING_TRANSPORT (default OFF,
byte-identical when off -- dserver-ring.c is an empty TU and the dserver-ring.h
call-site stubs fold away).

- dserver-ring.c/.h: libc-free (raw LINUX_SYSCALL only). __dserver_ring_try_attach
  builds a memfd holding the dserver_ring_shm control block + two SPSC rings,
  fills it, and negotiates via the generated ring_attach RPC (server validates +
  returns the wake eventfd). __dserver_ring_task_self_trap publishes a request
  onto the c2s ring, writes the wake eventfd, then bounded-spins (reusing the
  DARLING_GUEST_RECVSPIN budget) and FUTEX_WAITs (cross-process, NON-private) on
  s2c_futex for the reply; validates seq+callnum+length before trusting it; falls
  back to UDS on any miss. P3 scope: ONE ring per process owned by the first
  attaching thread (others UDS-fall-back) to sidestep fragile early-boot guest TLS;
  per-thread rings are P4. postfork_reset drops the parent ring in the child.

- mach_traps.c: __task_self_trap_rpc tries the ring first, falls back to the UDS
  wrapper (folds to the plain UDS path when the feature is off).

- fork.c: __dserver_ring_postfork_reset alongside the per-thread socket refresh.

- CMakeLists: option DARLING_RING_TRANSPORT compiled into BOTH emulation (dylib)
  and emulation_dyld (dyld), since the trap path lives in both.

The datapath logic + adversarial bounds-safety are proven by darlingserver's
host gate (ring_datapath_test, RED->GREEN under ASan), which compiles the SAME
rpc-supplement.h SPSC helpers this guest uses. The live guest<->server round
trip + the latency A/B require a coordinated dylib+dyld+server deploy (not done).

VERIFIED: dserver-ring.c / mach_traps.c / fork.c compile clean flag ON and OFF
in the dyld target. Nothing deployed/pushed; matching server side is
darlingserver perf/shmem-ring-abi-validator @5a73f80.
