From 1b1deba0069c4cf1a3908b83fe41ca1049e9937d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 15:46:56 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 Phase B Stage 1: default DARLING_RING_TRANSPORT ON
 for dev/nightly

Guest-side half of the product-authorized Stage-1 flip (paired with darlingserver's
DSERVER_RING_TRANSPORT). Flip ONLY the cmake option default OFF->ON; the single option drives
both targets (emulation -> dylib, emulation_dyld -> dyld). No source logic change, no new op,
no duplex. Frozen ring set only; destroy-capable ops stay UDS.

Rollback: this default back to OFF + rebuild. Release/prod packaging policy unchanged. Full
gate/smoke/perf matrix verified on the flip (see the darlingserver Stage-1 commit message).
