From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 03:22:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P8 D3 (dar-1il.3.1.1): guest duplex wait-pump +
 real-dylib selftest

Guest side of the end-to-end duplex selftest -- the last bridge between the
synthetic transport (D1/D2) and the real mach_port_deallocate problem. NO real
op rides the duplex lane yet (deallocate is Phase E, blocked on this being GREEN).

dserver-ring.c:
 - gr_duplex_pump_once(): handle ONE S2C ECHO upcall on the CALLER thread (compute
   the echo, publish the correlated reply, doorbell the server). RED hook
   -DDUPLEX_RED_NO_GUEST_PUMP disables it (gate's RED arm: pump dead -> no completion).
 - gr_duplex_wait_reply(): a gr_wait_reply sibling that pumps the S2C upcall mailbox
   while waiting for the parent final reply. CRITICAL: its slow-path FUTEX_WAIT is
   BOUNDED (50ms x 60 = ~3s cap, then give up) -- an unbounded wait would re-introduce
   the very deadlock the duplex lane exists to prevent if an upcall is ever lost.
 - __dserver_ring_duplex_selftest(): advertise DUPLEX_CAP_SELFTEST, publish the
   sentinel parent (DSERVER_RING_DUPLEX_SELFTEST_CALLNUM), run the pump, return the echo.
 - __dserver_ring_maybe_run_duplex_selftest(): one-shot driver gated by the env var
   DARLING_GUEST_DUPLEX_SELFTEST=1. SAFETY DISCIPLINE: the env is set ONLY on the
   per-command `darling shell` invocation against an already-warm server, NEVER at boot,
   so daemons (launchd/shellspawn) never inherit it and never run the selftest; only the
   targeted leaf does. Skips guest-pid 1 defensively.

mach_traps.c: call the one-shot driver from task_self_trap_impl (early, ring attached).

LIVE: booted guest prints
  [dring-duplex-selftest] PASS rc=0 arg=0xC0FFEE42 result=0x9AA5B418 expect=0x9AA5B418
(echo = arg ^ 0x5A5A5A5A). Pairs with the server commit (sentinel + _drainDuplexReply).
