From 7144b56d220fbff6b9d821d71cbf1ae24c4cd187 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 07:46:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P8 D6 (dar-1il.3.2.x): caller-S2C duplex SIDEBAND --
 guest (vm_deallocate-over-duplex + warm proof)

Guest half of the caller-S2C sideband. Two pieces:

1. __dserver_ring_mach_vm_deallocate_duplex: send mach_vm_deallocate over the
   duplex ring (vm_deallocate body {u32 target; u64 address; u64 size}, the
   DUPLEX_CAP_VM_DEALLOCATE cap), pumping any munmap S2C upcall on the caller
   thread via gr_duplex_wait_reply. Wired into _kernelrpc_mach_vm_deallocate_trap_impl
   ahead of the UDS path (a strict no-op unless armed). Once published it does NOT
   UDS-retry on timeout (avoids a double munmap of a possibly-reused range): the
   server owns the op, and vm_deallocate is idempotent on an unmapped range.

2. __dserver_ring_maybe_run_d6_munmap_proof: the synthetic WARM live-cure proof
   (default-OFF, env-gated DARLING_GUEST_D6_MUNMAP_PROOF=1 on the leaf -- the
   proven D3 trigger pattern, never inherited by daemons). Maps a real page, then
   sends vm_deallocate of it with target==mach_task_self() over the duplex ring,
   bypassing the trap's local-munmap gate; the server frees OUR map -> a REAL
   caller-S2C munmap rides the duplex mailbox -> the guest pump runs the real
   munmap(2) on this thread -> server fiber resumes -> final reply over the ring.
   Drives ring_duplex_s2c>0 LIVE (the cure D4/D5 could not get). Kept as the
   default-OFF live regression harness. gr_duplex_wait_reply gains a -DD6_RED_NO_PUMP
   compile gate (the no-pump RED arm: bounded, no s2c, no wedge).

The hazard's only real carrier in Darling is mach_msg_overwrite (OOL teardown),
which stays UDS-only -- no production op is migrated. NON-GOALS held: no
mod_refs/deallocate resurrection, no simple-ring op-set expansion, no
launchd-global duplex, no fabricated success.

Pairs with darlingserver D6 commit. NOTHING PUSHED.
