From 97e0e6cfbbfc91f1387779632436d9cc0340fcb0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 10:12:39 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 P8 D10 (dar-1il.5): migrate thread_self_trap +
 host_self_trap as Tier-2 no-fiber ring ops (guest)

Guest side of the D9-chosen migration. The two remaining pure-mint self-trap family
members get ring helpers + trap wiring, mirroring task_self_trap.

- dserver-ring.c: __dserver_ring_thread_self_trap / __dserver_ring_host_self_trap reuse
  gr_port_trap verbatim (byte-identical empty-request/uint32-port-reply shape). Each routes
  over the ring iff in DSERVER_RING_C2S_OPCODES (the shared allowlist); any transport miss
  -> caller UDS-falls-back.
- dserver-ring.h: declarations + folded-away stubs (return -1) for the non-ring build.
- mach_traps.c: thread_self_trap_impl / host_self_trap_impl try the ring first, UDS
  fallback on any miss. UNCACHED (unlike task_self_trap): thread_self_trap is per-thread;
  host_self_trap left uncached to keep this bead minimal -- the win is the ring transport
  (~4us->~1us), not caching (perf#7, orthogonal, fork-correctness risk).

LIVE (homebrew-test, D10 dylib+server): both ops moved 100% UDS -> mostly-ring
(already-on-ring), caller_s2c=0, ring clean; fork-storm 3/3; no wedge. ABI v5 unchanged
(opcode-hash auto-includes the new ops -> skewed guest rejected at attach -> all-UDS, proven
live + by the ring_attach_check gate). Server side committed separately in darlingserver.
Prod dylib restored after. NOTHING PUSHED.
