From b4e7110a777e5859ff8dfaff6348c14fc84a17ca Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 12:11:02 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 D13 (dar-1il.8): migrate mldr_path + vchroot_path to
 Lane-1 ring (guest)

The path ops have a char*/path UDS signature, but the path bytes are delivered by the
server via writeMemory (process_vm_writev) on the guest /proc/mem -- transport-agnostic.
So the ring request body is the FIXED 16B {uint64 buffer; uint64 buffer_size} and the
reply is 8B {uint64 length}, byte-identical to the generated dserver_call/reply_<op>_t.
NO arena, no variable payload.

- dserver-ring.c: __dserver_ring_vchroot_path + __dserver_ring_mldr_path via gr_full_trap
  (fixed body + fixed reply, transport-miss -> UDS fallback).
- dserver-ring.h: decls + folded-away (ring-off) stubs returning -1.
- vchroot_userspace.c (init_vchroot_path, WARM post-attach site): try-ring-then-UDS,
  #ifndef TEST-guarded (the experiment TEST build has no ring). The mldr.c:940 caller is
  in the mldr binary (no ring) and stays UDS by construction.
- execve.c (sys_execve): try-ring-then-UDS, preserving the site's exact result semantics.

set_executable_path NOT migrated (pre-attach mldr-only + NO_REPLY). Pairs with
darlingserver @88f2727. Built clean, symbols present, live A/B GREEN, fork-storm 3/3.
NOT pushed.
