From 4368016ed1f2e825493b9db4aad8367b3b7da2e7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 14:54:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] perf#18 D17 (dar-dar6x4-perf-5dq / dar-1il.12): guest
 per-thread lane stats (recon)

RECON-only, default-OFF. Adds guest-side per-thread lane stats to answer D17's lane-exhaustion
question from the guest: g_stat_lanes_acquired / _exhausted / _reclaimed (bumped on the slow
attach path, never the hot publish path) + __dserver_ring_lane_stats_dump() on the clean exit
path (sys_exit, mirroring __darling_rpc_sleep_dump so it is robust without a dylib fini handler),
gated DARLING_GUEST_LANE_STATS=1 (libc-free /proc/self/environ scan; strict no-op otherwise).

Live (matched build): every leaf process reports acquired=1 exhausted=0 reclaimed=0 held_now=1
-> reason C (lane exhaustion) is conclusively 0; the post-D16 residual is not exhaustion.

No behavior change: the counters are pure stats, the dump is no-op unless armed, and nothing on
the hot path is touched. ABI v5 unchanged.
---
 .../resources/dserver-ring.h                  |  6 ++
 .../resources/dserver-ring.c                  | 72 +++++++++++++++++++
 .../src/xnu_syscall/bsd/impl/unistd/exit.c    |  9 +++
 3 files changed, 87 insertions(+)

diff --git a/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/include/linux_premigration/resources/dserver-ring.h b/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/include/linux_premigration/resources/dserver-ring.h
index 2f6d0a8d73b71ac550ea22ae3bea3a2d35e50c47..c1669af7027a5ab00711431c9cdd0b0aebaa6dae 100644
--- a/darling/src/libsystem_kernel/emulation/include/linux_premigration/resources/dserver-ring.h
